# Async Error Handling

Always handle errors in async code!

## Try/Catch with Async/Await

```javascript
async function safeOperation() {
    try {
        const data = await riskyOperation();
        return data; // Success
    } catch (error) {
        return 'fallback'; // Error handled
    }
}
```

## Real World Scenario
When calling an external API service, it might be down or return a 500 error. Your test shouldn't crash; instead, it should catch the error and perhaps log it or retry, or at least fail gracefully with a meaningful message.

